    "overview": "Tanglin Trust School is a co-educational day school in Singapore, established in 1925. It is the oldest British school in Southeast Asia. The school follows the English National Curriculum and is the only school in Singapore to offer both A Level and IB Diploma pathways in Sixth Form. Tanglin operates as a not-for-profit trust, with all tuition fees directed back into the school. Approximately 2,800 students from over 50 nationalities are enrolled across Infant, Junior, and Senior schools on its Portsdown Road campus.",
    "editorial": "Tanglin Trust is widely regarded as the strongest British school in Singapore. Parents on Reddit and expat forums consistently cite high academic standards, particularly at A Level and IB. The school regularly achieves strong university placement to Russell Group and Ivy League institutions. Some parents note that demand significantly exceeds supply, with waitlists common in popular year groups. A small number of forum posts mention high fees and a competitive social environment, but these are minority views and do not constitute a pattern of serious concern.",
